ColtExpress December 2021

The results in the tabs below show the MCTS parameters optimised against each of three opponents:

  • Random (RND)
  • One Step Lookahead (OSLA) that optimises the score immediately after the next move
  • An MCTS agent with 20ms computational budget per decision (Rollout and Tree depth of 10, K = 1.41, using classic Open-Loop UCB with SelfOnly search)

The MCTS agent being optimised has 40ms per decision. In each case 30 independent runs of NTBEA are used, with 4,500 trials in each (out of a total parameter-space size of 48,000). Hence we have 30 independent recommendations in each case, and we plot the marginal distribution of each. If all 30 use the same value then we can be confident this is pretty critical to good performance. If the distribution is flat over all values, then that suggests the parameter is not important at all.

The data below are for each Opponent (RND, OSLA, MCTS, MultiNTBEA) using the default heuristic; plus for each player count (2P, 3P, 4P) on the same basis. On each tab there are three sets of information:

  1. Win Rates. Each of the 30 NTBEA runs produces a single recommendation - 900 games are run using this setting to get a win rate. The reported win rate is the average of these 30 individual results. [No Win Rate is reported for MultiNTBEA runs, as there is no standard opponent against which this can be measured.]

  2. Fingerprints

  3. p-Values for Chi-squared tests of homogeneity for each parameter. For ease of visualisation a hard threshold of a p-value less than 0.001 is used here.

The core conclusions are:

  • Using the default heuristic gives a pretty dreadful player. It only wins 31% of 4-P games against a RND player for example!
  • Rollout Length is the only significant parameter across all player counts and opponents: Colt Express needs long rollouts of 10+ for 2P and 30+ for 3/4P to play well (or at least as well as the weak heuristic allows).
  • MultiNTBEA gives a very flat set of parameter recommendations. None of them are significant at the 0.001 level.
